   Non-Communist Parties Condemn NATO Attack 

   Leaders of non-communist parties and non-party-affiliation noted
   figures held a forum here today and strongly condemned the NATO attack
   on the Chinese embassy in Belgrade, the capital of Yugoslavia, Friday
   night.

   Speaking at the forum, the non-communist party leaders and individuals
   expressed their firm support for the solemn and just statement by the
   Chinese government.

   The central committees of the eight non-communist parties also
   published their announcements on the issue today expressing their
   support for the government's stance and condemning the U.S.-led NATO
   brutal attack on the Chinese embassy.
